{
  "doc_id": "965",
  "text": "If we choose the classical superpotential to be a polynomial of the form W Λ (φ) ∼ O (φ n ) with leading power n even, we expect spontaneous supersymmetry breaking to occur during the flow towards the IR [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . It is known that spontaneous supersymmetry breaking is an IR effect, where the ground state is lifted to E 0 > 0 [CITATION_4] .",
